# No Cowboy Coding — Triage Gate (CRITICAL)

## Rule

When the user reports, discovers, or mentions something NEW during a conversation — a bug,
improvement idea, new feature, or unexpected behavior — the agent MUST route it to triage.
The agent MUST NOT plan, architect, or implement it inline.

## What counts as "something new"

- A bug the user just found
- An improvement idea
- A new feature request
- Unexpected behavior discovered during development
- Any demand that is NOT already tracked in docs/ROADMAP.md, docs/ISSUES.md, or docs/FINDINGS.md

## What the agent MUST do

1. Acknowledge the finding
2. Inform the user: "Isso precisa passar pela triagem antes de implementar."
3. Either:
   a. Run triage inline via `/triagem [descricao]` (routes to PMO mode TRIAR), OR
   b. Generate a triage prompt for a new chat:
      /triagem — [brief description of what the user reported]
4. NEVER skip to technical planning (listing files to modify, proposing architecture, writing code)

## What the agent MUST NOT do

- Propose a technical plan for the new item
- List files to create/modify for the new item
- Start implementing the new item
- Create enum values, services, pages, or any code for the new item
- Offer "Quer que eu implemente?" for unregistered items

## What this rule does NOT block

- Active sprint tasks from docs/ROADMAP.md — continue normally
- Active corrections from docs/FINDINGS.md via /fix — continue normally
- Trivial in-context fixes (typos, lint errors, import fixes) while working on a tracked task
- Investigations to help classify — but must NOT jump to implementation
- Questions/explanations — answering "how does X work?" is always allowed

## How to distinguish

| Situation | Action |
|-----------|--------|
| User asks to implement task from ROADMAP | Proceed — tracked task |
| User reports a bug during sprint work | Acknowledge, route to triage, continue sprint work |
| User says "seria legal ter X" | Acknowledge, route to triage |
| User finds a bug while coding a tracked task | Acknowledge, route to triage, continue tracked task |
| Agent discovers a bug during audit | Register in FINDINGS.md per audit-separation rule |
| User asks "como funciona X?" | Answer normally — it's a question |

## Why

Without this gate:
- Items bypass ISSUES.md/FINDINGS.md/BACKLOG.md — PMO loses visibility
- Items bypass ROADMAP.md — no sprint planning, no dependency check
- Items bypass the Architect — no architectural review for large changes
- The project accumulates untracked work and technical debt

## The correct flow for new items

User reports something new
  → PMO TRIAR classifies (BUG / MELHORIA / FEATURE / INVESTIGACAO)
    → BUG/MELHORIA: ISSUES.md + FINDINGS.md → /fix
    → FEATURE (now): ISSUES.md → ROADMAP.md → sprint
    → FEATURE (later): BACKLOG.md → implement when ready
    → INVESTIGACAO: ISSUES.md → diagnose first
